- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed function computation and proposes a novel token-based approach for the same. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the proposed approach involves tokens travelling across the network. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with computation in networks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for function computation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with distributed systems and proposes a new algorithm for the same.
